```{r}
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
```
```{r}
mydata <- read.csv("all-semi-unique.csv")
nrow(mydata)
ncol(mydata)
names(mydata)
head(mydata)
tail(mydata)
summary(mydata)
```
From Summary it can be viewed that the add columns have only one value for all the observations. Perform data cleaning and remove them.

```{r}
mydata <- subset.data.frame(mydata, select = -c(ad.aid, ad.lid, ad.g, ad.bgcl, ad.bgcls, ad.fncl, ad.fncls, ad.logo, ad.logo2x, ad.cm, ad.logoAndroidS, ad.logoAndroidH, ad.url))
summary(mydata)
```
